msgid ""
"Each of the supported databases contains different JDBC URL configuration options.\n"
"Going into each of those options is beyond the scope of this document,\n"
"but the following section gives an overview of each database URL and a link to the official documentation."
msgstr ""

#: /home/ynojima/playground/ja.quarkus.io/build/jekyll-source/_versions/2.13/guides/datasource.adoc
msgid ""
"Derby is an embedded database.\n"
"It can run as a server, based on a file, or live completely in memory.\n"
"All of these options are available as listed above.\n"
"You can find more information at the https://db.apache.org/derby/docs/10.8/devguide/cdevdvlp17453.html#cdevdvlp17453[official documentation]."
msgstr ""

#: /home/ynojima/playground/ja.quarkus.io/build/jekyll-source/_versions/2.13/guides/datasource.adoc
msgid ""
"H2 is an embedded database.\n"
"It can run as a server, based on a file, or live completely in memory.\n"
"All of these options are available as listed above.\n"
"You can find more information at the https://h2database.com/html/features.html?highlight=url&search=url#database_url[official documentation]."
msgstr ""

